700130f-b.text:
E. 149th Strect, north sidem east from Anthony J, Briffin Place. At this point the street is above the New York Central and'New Haven railroad tracks. The tall building is the ten-story Terminal Building, near the northeast corner of Park Avenue. View 2 shows the low buiding at the northeast corner of Park Avenue. View 3 is east from
the Terminal Building.
P. L. Sperr  April 28, 1941
NO RERODUCTIONS  Views 1, 2, 3
